  "original_title": "\u2018\u0ba8\u0bcb-\u0b9f\u0bc0\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bae\u2019 \u0baa\u0bcb\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8 \u0b85\u0b95\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1 \u0ba4\u0bc0\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Resolution to eliminate the 'No-Deal Kama' protest",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "COLOMBO - Anti-government protesters have decided to remove the 'No-Deal Gama' protest site set up in front of the Prime Minister's official residence, Alarimalika, in the Kollupitiya area.",
        "After the appointment of Ranil Wickremesinghe as Prime Minister in May 2022, the 'No-Deal Coma' protest was formed by anti-government protesters.",
        "Ranil Wickremesinghe was appointed Prime Minister by former President Gotabaya Rajapaksa after former Prime Minister Mahinda Rajapaksa resigned as Prime Minister following the May 09 violence.",
        "In this case, after Ranil Wickremesinghe was sworn in as the Prime Minister, the anti-government protesters set up a 'No-Deal Kama' protest site in front of the Alari House.",
        "It is noteworthy that as Ranil Wickremesinghe has been sworn in today as the 8th executive president of Sri Lanka, the protestors have decided to remove the protest site from that area."
      ],
